core:processNote.core:description: If there is an exception while processing the retry, just move it to failed immediately
If we failed to enqueue into the Failed queue, we try and roll-back the read - this will mean we will attempt to reprocess the message again in the next loop

This process is the main process that manages the MultiThreadedConfigurableQueueConsumer.
It deals with re-queuing the retry messages onto the primary queue, and initialises the threads. Each thread is managed by the MultiThreadedThread process.
For the re-queueing process to work, it expects the messages in the retry queue to be special 'retry message' wrapper classes. This should be done by the MultiThreadedPayloadHandler when it pushes the messages onto the retry queue.

If we get an exception here, that would mean we've posted the message (successfully) to the failed queue, but have failed to commit the read from the retry queue. We stop the processor in this case as otherwise we could flood the failed queue with the same message

The tools incorrectly report an error about the mapping to ThreadGroupName in the StartThreads action. This is a bug and has been raised in https://enactor.atlassian.net/browse/DT-212. The ThreadGroupName ends up being set correctly when the code runs.
